The paper proposes a method for sequential recommendation, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the challenges of modeling user interests from sparse feedback, which is a problem in social networks and online communities (cs.SI).
